    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Differential Case and Ring Gear - Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, install a new anti-lock speed sensor ring with a dead blow hammer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a71" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the anti-lock speed sensor ring on the case flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a72" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner side gear thrust washer and inner side gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a73" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062246.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the pinion gear cross shaft with the pin hole vertical position.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a74" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062245.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lightly lubricate all of the mating surfaces with clean axle lubricant. This will aid in assembly
                    and provide initial lubrication.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st pinion gear thrust washer and pinion gear on the pinion cross shaft.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Use SAE 75W-140 High Performance Rear Axle Lubricant or equivalent.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a75" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062244.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd pinion gear and pinion gear thrust washer on the differential cross shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a76" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062243.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the differential cross shaft lock pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a77" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062242.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There is no thrust washer in this location.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer side gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a78" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062241.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Apply Stud and Bearing Mount TA-27 or equivalent to the differential ring gear bolts.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the ring gear and the differential case bolt holes. Install the differential ring gear
                bolts in the holes finger tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a79" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0062219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tool and a shop press, press the differential assembly half on the
                differential ring gear half.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a80" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023954.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the differential ring gear bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten to 204 Nm (150 lb-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a81" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023955.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tools, install the ring gear side carrier bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a82" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023956.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tools, install the differential side carrier bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a83" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023957.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully position the differential assembly into the carrier housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The bearing cups must seat on the differential side bearings.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Align the match marks.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The bolt threads must be clean.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the differential bearing caps.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a84" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020649.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Position the bearing cap onto the leg.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Apply High Strength Threadlocker TA-26 to the differential bearing cap bolt
                    threads and install the differential bearing cap bolts.
                    <callout2 type="alpha">Use Threadlock&#174; 262 TA-26 or equivalent.</callout2>
                    <callout2 type="alpha">Tighten the differential bearing cap bolts enough to eliminate visible space
                        between the differential bearing cap and leg. Do not tighten the differential bearing cap bolts
                        to the appropriate torque at this time.
                    </callout2>
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Align the differential assembly within the bearing bores before applying preload or damage to the
                    bearings will result.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the differential bearing adjusting rings.</para>
            <para>&#8226; Tighten both adjusting rings until there is zero end play, and some backlash between the
                differential ring gear and pinion. Make sure the adjusting ring tooth aligns so that installation of the
                adjusting ring cotter pin is possible.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a85" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1941A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the backlash at zero.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The adjusting ring tooth must always align so that installation of the adjusting ring cotter
                        pin is possible.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Loosen the adjusting ring on the tooth side of the differential ring gear one tooth, and tighten the
                opposite adjusting ring one tooth. Repeat this process until backlash is at zero.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a86" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1916A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the backlash and the bearing preload to specifications.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>With a new matched set installed, set the backlash to the specification.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>With the original matched set installed, set the backlash to the specification recorded prior
                        to disassembly.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">NOTE: The adjusting ring tooth must always align so that installation of the
                            adjusting ring cotter pin is possible.
                        </emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>Tighten the adjusting ring on the tooth side of the differential ring gear until backlash is
                        within specifications.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a87" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1916A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the differential ring gear and pinion backlash in 4 equally spaced positions around
                the differential ring gear.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>The acceptable backlash tolerance is &#177; 0.0508 mm (0.002 inch) from the backlash
                        specification.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If the backlash tolerance varies more than 0.080 mm (0.003 inch) between the 4 positions,
                        remove the differential and determine the cause.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a88" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1916A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the bolts.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten to 190 Nm (140 lb-ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Check the differential ring gear and pinion backlash, as described in the previous step, after
                        tightening the bolts.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a89" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1920A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the adjusting ring cotter pins.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a90" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0023952.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear anti-lock brake sensor, if equipped.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten to 27 Nm (20 lb-ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0502a91" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1917A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
